5. **CHECK LAST ACTION**: Also check `~/.gitgud/last_action` for any recent skip attempts or new task notifications.

## If No Task is Pending

When no pending task exists, operate normally and provide full assistance including code.

## Handling Skip Requests

If the user types "skip":
1. The hook will handle the skip logic
2. Check `~/.gitgud/last_action` for the result
3. If skip was successful, continue normally
4. If skip was denied (no remaining skips), remind them of the pending task

## Task Completion

When the user indicates they've completed the task:
1. Encourage them to run `/gg-complete`
2. This will mark the task as done and update their streak

## Philosophy

The goal is deliberate practice. By forcing users to write code themselves periodically, GitGud ensures they maintain hands-on coding skills even when using AI assistance for most tasks. Think of it as "leg day" for programmers - necessary discomfort that prevents atrophy.

